caption: The food was delicious, the atmosphere was great, very clean inside, staff was very friendly. The playlist alone was fire, really good variety. I would go back just to hang out and vibe. REALLY good experience.

Great food. I visited Yolk on a Sunday morning after a few drinks the night before and it’s just what I needed. It was a little bit pricey and my table were waiting a while to be seated. Food was good quality and staff were kind and talkative. Overall a great place for Sunday brunch but I won’t be going every weekend.
I like the idea of them trying out new recipes but they didn’t seem to care much for guest feedback. Service was good and food wasn’t much different than most brunch places.

Went here for brunch and was not disappointed! The oat milk latte I had was absolutely amazing, along with the breakfast Mac and cheese being great also! My only drawback would have to be the service unfortunately. It seems like they were trying to rush us, but even with that, we had a great time! Definitely recommend checking it out!

So this was my first time going to the test kitchen and I how to say that I have been to other Yolk locations and I like them. So I was anticipating a similar experience. Our server Colleen was amazing very, helpful very, And insightful very accommodating. Note that we  asked for augmentations on virtually everything we ordered. The food came and the presentation was gorgeous, as you will see by the pictures, and it tastes even better than i expected. I genuinely appreciate it the quantity of condiments are forgiven, note that with the white chocolate macadamia nut pancakes that were covered in Melba sauce (which was delicious) they gave me syrup which was Overkill but appreciated.
Yummy food and drinks. My server was great. Perfect location to grab a bite before hitting Aldi for shopping.
My favorite breakfast place in the city... always a new and funky menu being the test kitchen and very pleasant staff!

Solid brunch place in the area. I like the test kitchen because there are always new to try. We always try and get something off the test menu to keep it fresh, but their standard options are delicious too. BYOB which we love, but be prepared to maybe wait a little
Menu price was different than the bill. They apologized and said things need to get updated but didn't offer to refund the difference (about 10%). Deceptive and appropriate action not taken

I ordered fried chicken and biscuits with sausage gravy and 1 sunnyside up egg. The chicken was nicely cook, the biscuits very soft and good,  the egg very good.  The gravy little disappointed as didn't have much flavor and didn’t have sausage.  The koren fried chicken that comes with small waffles was good, just the chicken had a sauce that tasted just like buffalo sauce, need a little more of the cabbage salad. The red velvet French toast were better in the past, this time the cream cheese frosting tasted more like pastry cream,but not bad. Bacon and sausage are good!!. I paid 72 dollars, so is little more expensive than average but is very good

Great food, friendly waiter, low key vibe, early 90's music!!! Felt like I was in 7th grade again....the good parts.
Excellent food. Every dish that I've tried has been delicious.
Great place for breakfast or lunch.  Use Yelp and book ahead. Wait times can be long.

Service: General, A balance of welcoming, professional, and proper.  Food: Yolk All Star Breakfast: Bacon was well cooked and not salty Crepes were delicious and filling Sausages were flavorful and not greasy Scrambled eggs were on point  Facility: Safe, and well illuminated very clean cut, cafeteria style.  I was served by D'mitry who was on point with service and deserves high praise from management.  I give this place 5/5 and highly recommend this restaurancr

Great little spot in a newly developed area of Wicker Park. The food was great, I came with a party of 4 and we all really liked our meals. it’s a test kitchen so the menu is a little more innovation. We ordered the chicken and waffles, BLT, and the cheesy (egg sandwich). The bacon on the BLT was exceptional, it had chunks of real bacon, not strips, that were cooked beautifully. The fruit sides were also very fresh, and did not include honeydew or cantaloupe (to me this is a positive as I think those fruits never taste good in a fruit salad, are cheap, and are usually underripe). I also got the iced horchata oat milk latte, which was pretty good, though it was $6 and 75% ice so I wouldn’t recommend their iced drinks. It is a little on the higher end of price range for breakfast (expect to pay around $15 or more for an entree, and about $6 or more for any speciality coffee drink), but you can taste the quality difference.
Very good.......

This place was super adorable inside and we were very excited to eat here! But when we showed up, the lady told us there was a 40 minute wait for only my husband and I to get a table. We decided to wait it out. As they called group after group (who had come in long after us), we still waited. We were waiting well over an hour and even talked to the hostess a few times, but never were given a table. Finally just grabbed a coffee and walked to chipotle. Disappointing, since this place was well-rated and the place looked nice. 😕  Side note, after walking a few blocks, ordering meals, and eating our food, we walked back to our car and happened to look in the window of the cafe... and a couple who had been seated long before we left STILL had no food! We were glad we had chosen to move on😅

Made my salad to order, but they added a dressing I didn’t ask for.  Plus, $3 for strawberries to be added?!  $45 for a custom made salad, oat milk latte and a tasteless omelette was just too much.  The gluten free bread was great, get where before 9:30 on a Sunday if you don’t like waiting.

Today's service and food were basic at best. Our order was taken wrong, my grits were cold, and the waitress seemed so disinterested in serving my son and I. Which is rather sad because I come to this location a bit and haven't experienced this before. Perhaps the young lady was having a rough morning. It was around 8 am-9 am. She seemed to be busy with a few tables by herself so this may have played a part in her disdain for us. Nevertheless, it doesn't help business and keep customers wanting to come back. I will be back ...just not in the early morning for sure.
Loved the food, unique options and the wait is pretty short with the app. Coffee and chai drinks were not as great.

If you are looking for a place to try a different type of brunch, then the Yolk Test Kitchen is the place to be. Today we had the opportunity to try it again for brunch. It had been a while since we've been and after going to the dentist, we needed some sustenance in our tummies and pronto! So we decided to go to the Test Kitchen. Thankfully we didn't have to wait long to be seated and we had a fabulous waitress named Rani to take care of us. We each ordered something different... the hubby chilaquiles, the daughter Nutella crepes and I got their California omelet. (Pictures attached) The hubby ordered an eggnog cold brew and I got the Americano coffee. I have to say that I was VERY impressed with that eggnog cold brew, it was so much better to drink than my Americano! LOL! The Americano was a little too strong for my taste but the hubby liked it. When our food arrived, everything was perfect! The food was nice & hot and beyond tasty! Rani was there to answer questions about the food and even told us about some other items on the menu that we can try. She was a great person to talk to. I haven't had a bad meal there... and I hope that I never do. The first time we went, we have their KFB which is fried pork belly..  OMG, it was amazing!  A side note... when our plates were being picked up, a made a comment to the young man that I wished that they sold their jam. He said that he would ask the manager if they did. He comes back to let us know that they do and asked if we wanted to purchase some! Oh yes!!! Homemade jam is MY JAM!! LOL! We got the jam, paid and left with a "Happy New Year" from the barista!  People are just great there... can't wait to go back!

Yolk's Test Kitchen is my favorite brunch spot in town, I take all guests here and it's my first suggestion if someone wants to meet up on a weekend. My current favorite dish is the Korean Hot Chicken and Waffles, but everything is so good my favorite thing will change every time we go. Go get your brunch on here, this place is great!

Love this spot for brunch. You are able to try out new dishes before they are on the Yolk menu. Excellent coffee bar with new flavors, always something fun. If you are going during the week-end, I recommend getting there early as it does get busy.
Great breakfast fare, not far off the blue line.

The description says cheery & it truly is! The staff here are incredible! They all walk around smiling. Such a welcoming & bustling spot with i n c r e d i b l e food. I mean, really good. This is also in a great spot around Wicker Park and super convenient to walk to from this area. Close to cute shops & coffee spots. Great vibes & big windows letting in tons of work.
The BLT and the Avalon Chicken Sandwich was one of the best dishes that I try on this place really amazing experience will love it to come back.
It was delicious , fruit was fresh everything was great the server was wonderful I can say it was a little pricey
Great restaurant with some unique food options. It gets very busy on the weekends, plan ahead!
Food is delicious

I come here just for the breakfast Mac and cheese and this is the third time I come in on either a Monday or Tuesday and they always run out by 10 or 11!  I think if it’s a popular dish you guys should have back up of it, it’s not right to sell out by that time if it’s a breakfast restaurant!
Great food and service but coffee is too strong.

Amazing. Variety of menu might seem intimidating at first, but you can't go wrong with any item. Plenty of healthy options and the decor is splendid. I will be back

Great food and service. Breakfast mac 'cheese and avocado toast were awesome! Free street parking a bonus. Food seemed better than the average Yolk, but they never let you down either. Great idea to do the "test kitchen".
Always great service and delicious food!
Food was pretty good, service felt more like a fast food restaurant.
Great coffee for to go!
Good food. ..
Love having breakfast here when in Chicago.
You have to try their chicken and biscuits and they are Korean waffles.

As all other Yolk locations, this one offers a great food selection, good quantities and decent quality. They do test a lot of dishes here before they roll them out to other locations, so it's always a good place to try something new. The chicken was amazing and I also enjoyed the challah french toast.
Great food, great service, we love this place!
Very good food, this is where you can find new menu items being tested. Service was great too.
Delicious food  very friendly going back

Soooooo good! Always loved Yolk, but this is next level yummy. I had fried chicken over biscuits and gravy with a sunny side egg. My guy had killer Korean fried chicken with mini waffles. Fresh beet/orange juice was delicious and not something you can get everywhere. I had THE hardest time choosing what to eat because it all looked so good. Cant wait to come back and try more.
Very good food and an overall awesome experience. I will be coming back to try as much of the Test Kitchen menu as possible
Fun place. Wide selection of food!
Food is always good but service today was def subpar. We think our waitress forgot to put our order in since three tables that were seated after us were done eating by the time our food arrived.
Amazing brunch place!
Soo good.
The best place ever, you need to try it , enjoy!

Fun place with flavorful options, test menu is what attracted me. The kfb bites are pork belly tots and great, but are greasy so it will drain your appetite. Eggs are buttery, chewy/meaty bacon. Korean chicken is more buffalo flavor but great. Basics are pretty standard fare, but have more exciting options than diners. Nick was our server and great. Although new, he definitely helped us navigate menu items and made strong coffee. Thank you for the ❤ in my mocha!
Great menu and kitchen.  The cold brew was almost all ice...my only complaint.
First time trying the test kitchen. Got the red velvet french toast, the country Skillet and the eggs Benedict. Coffee was nice and hot.

Just stumbled in here because I was having a business meeting and starving. The place we had planned to meet didn't have food. I was pleasantly surprised at how deloghtful the server was. And even though they're a breakfast joint they had 2 salads.  I had the southwest salad with buffalo chicken and I loved it! Il definitely be back!
Great menu options and coffee, I had a chicken and waffles, it was very good, lil spicy but excellent..

Is good , service ok , but they want to charge you for everything, I know is a business, but you ask for creamers and the server said , oh we do creamers but is an extra charge for that , a mean really . I'm a hospitality industry and for my customer Im never gonna extra charge for those little things.

I have now been to Yolk several times. I get that it's a test kitchen, but it sure seems like the staff are test as well. I have had disinterested to rude service each time I have gone. This last time was the worst though, as I ordered a coffee that never showed. Halfway through the meal I asked again, and got it, with no offer for a refill when it was emptied. We were never given a third silverware wrap for the third person at our table (a table for four mind you). We ended up taking another water off a table near us, when our water ran out. Our server was busy, but seemed disinterested at best. Two of our three meals were brought by a runner, who never returned with the third meal. We had nearly finished our meals when the server finally showed up to check on us, realizing the third meal never arrived. The manager gave us $2.00 off the meal that arrived for our third person, as we finished our other meals, which we didn't even ask for. The food was eh-okay. It's Chicago, there are a thousand other places you could go, I would recommend trying any one of them before coming here. 2-stars for the tasty hot sauce and the red-velvet pancakes I ordered the first time I went. Before you think I am just some jerk who either has too high of standards and/or leaves bad reviews for wanting something in return: 1) This is one of a few bad reviews I have EVER left for a place out of the hundreds I have reviewed. 2) I did 7+ years working in all aspects of restaurants through high school and college. I know what good service is and what bad service is. This one is the latter. The pretty good food definitely does not make up for that in a place like Chicago. I usually give the benefit of the doubt, but several bad experiences tipped me over the edge on this one.
Korean Hot Chicken and Waffles not great, not awful,  decent..
Cool spot, good food
Good but not great.  Servings are much too large.

10/10 great place!
Loved the brunch options here. Omlettes, French toast are too good. Love the dining and setup. Service is good. Definitely recommended.
Meh. I like the regular yolk better. Even though they have most of the original menu on the back.

I had a great experience here!  The server who helped me was friendly, smiled and communicative. The AGM, Tiffany is a very sweet soul with a pleasant smile. She came up to see how my meal was and we enjoyed a 10-15 minute friendly conversation that brightened both of our days!  😊. I will be back.
Food was delicious. The atmosphere is nice. The service was good. The menu is not big because it's one of the smaller locations.

Good food, hash was really tasty and always appreciate the perfectly poached eggies. It is not, in any real sense, a test kitchen. Who associates breakfast with industrial precision, anyway, and why would you want to? My recommendation is to ditch the pretense. Good day, and two thumbs up.

This is a great place ... clean, great staff and great food.  I had the eggs Benedict with fresh strawberry orange juice... it was delicious. . Eggs perfectly poach.. a must try.. the staff was friendly, polite and very attentive.  My server answer all of my questions. I will definitely come back.

Yolk is my favorite restaurant. You can get bacon, sausage, eggs, pancakes, or a skillet anywhere. But Yolk does it all, but with a whole lot more! The staff of wonderful servers and cooks, are artists. Food is an expression of the people cooking it. You can eat anything from “so spicy your mouth will burn,” to “so sweet it will warm you up.” You actually feel the good vibes while eating there. Yolk is a Chicago staple. They have branched off to different states, as well!  Stop in to one of their restaurants, you will not be disappointed. Peace and love, Yolk rules!! ——Jon
Quick casual and delicious!
Amazing, friendly, helpful staff — Large portions and great food. Very comfortable atmosphere too!
Things are usually very very good. One time I had a mediocre short rib benedict, but everything else has been great!

Bland.  I can get behind the idea of a test kitchen if they really trying to push boundaries - I won't be mad if something doesn't work, but you have to try.  All of the did was simply bland.  The only interesting thing we had was the fried bacon.  However, they were plated with what tasted like cocktail sauce, so I couldn't stop thinking I was eating shrimp, which isn't really a breakfast food.   Still, I'm glad they tried, and I'd recommend anyone try it - just ask for the sauce on the side.
Very interesting selection of choices. Not your average restuarant!  When you want to be a little adventurous, head on over!

The barista said it was entered as a latte, as if it was my fault. I told her that's fine, but I ordered mochas. She told me to wait because she had other orders to complete. Great food, but poor execution. First, you stand in line to order your food. Then they give you your number and tell you to find a table. Then you wait... once the food comes out you realize that you forgot to stop at the water station and grab your own silverware. Point is, it's breakfast. You're usually hungover and want someone to serve you breakfast. I had to do everything except make it. My meal was really good, but I'm totally not a fan of doing everything myself. In my opinion, you failed this test. Not too late to change things up though.

The often present wait on a weekend for brunch is totally worth it. Yolk has a perfect mix of traditional fare and new twists on old standards. What's more, it adds new pairings with an innovative bent. Pick either breakfast or lunch offerings. Place your order at the register first and then you'll be seated (people sometimes mistakenly follow normal convention and go to a table first expecting to be waited on for the order. But the Test Kitchen's posted sign - which can be hard to see with a crowd- makes clear not to do that.)
Really yummy and creative breakfast food  menu everything we ordered was delicious

This place is quite different than their normal restaurants. You order at the counter and then they bring you the food. Everyone seemed to enjoy what they were eating, especially as we tried to order off their test kitchen menu and not the standard one. The reason why I only rated it three stars was because there was a bug in my greens. Apparently, it wasn’t the first time that it happened and it had something to do with them not being washed enough. The manager was great about it though, so my experience was saved. Overall, a good concept and I’m glad it was open to the public.

Can't wait for the pancake of the month, every month.  Chilaquilles are amazing and they've taken bacon to a new level.

Food was amazing! Service was quick and staff were friendly!
Delicious food,  fresh and tasty. Bright and clean. Kid friendly.

I love the set up! You order at the counter first, then find a table and they bring your food. Such creative options, but they also have the staples. I got the egg white breakfast sandwich and my friend got the Korean chicken and waffles- both deserve 5 stars! YUM! My husband and I also went a few weeks ago- I got the breakfast burrito and it was standard, very good. He got the shakshuka- one of our favorites when we are oven in Israel.
